snippet.textDisplay:
Say what you want about Matt Murray, but he played well again. I know, three goals in the 1st and that is the point at which he should have been drawn and quartered at center ice between periods. He is "garbage", "useless", "no-good" etc. etc. etc. In all seriousness, after the team calmed itself and the odd man rushes and goals scored by his own team mates ended, he was a stone wall. I can guarantee that if Jarry had been in goal the excuses would be endless. Every goal would be excused because they were simply someone else's fault. (likely Matt Murray himself!)



I don't know why we cannot accept that the Pens have two very good GT's and be happy that the team is so fortunate to be in this situation. How lucky are we as fans to know that as the Penguins roll into the playoffs they have two guys that are more than capable of playing like Murray did tonight? Jarry has been a bit shaky lately, something that can be expected and does not mean he is "garbage", it means he is human.



I like both players and am excited to see them both performing well. This has been a great season and could well end with another Cup to add to the Pens list. We fans should be supportive of the entire team and stand behind them all. The negative comments about players are good for nothing.

snippet.textDisplay: What a battle!  Great come back!  Murray looked sharp after a shaky 1st period performance but found his mojo.  Very physical game.
